{
  "doc_id": "35608",
  "text": "In this work we have identified an association between À634C IL-6 variant and HAM/TSP unlike what was related before [CITATION_1] . A previous study in Japan showed an association between the À634G IL-6 variant and the development of Human T-cell leukemia/lymphoma virus type 1 (HTLV-1) associated myelopathy [CITATION_2] . This conflicting result could be due to ethnic's differences. In fact, few studies have investigated the À634C/G IL-6 gene polymorphism, and all had been carried out in Asian populations. Recently, we demonstrated a lower frequency of the À634C IL-6 allele among individuals from Salvador (a city with a high racial admixture and a main contribution from African ancestry) than that observed previously in Asians [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
